results.name: Decimal expansion of 5 + sqrt(26).
comment: Continued fraction expansion of 5 + sqrt(26) is A010692.
This is the shape of a 10-extension rectangle; see A188640 for definitions. - _Clark Kimberling_, Apr 09 2011
link: Daniel Starodubtsev, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000
formula: Equals exp(arcsinh(5)), since arcsinh(x) = log(x + sqrt(x^2 + 1)). - _Stanislav Sykora_, Nov 01 2013
xref: Cf. A010481 (decimal expansion of sqrt(26)), A010692 (all 10's sequence).
results.author: _Klaus Brockhaus_, Apr 24 2010
